{
  "stem": "868.3",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And we said, look, we can consider us luck-- luckier than most, because both of us escaped.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Out of all the people in that garrison, the two of us escaped.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And maybe father will be equally lucky being that he is sick, maybe they will treat him gently.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I also had asked Don Giovanni that next morning to go immediately to the garrison and ask to speak to my father, counting on the appearance of a clergyman.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And if that would not succeed, I give him a little note, telling my father both his sons are safe and wrap it in a stone.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I told him at which part of the wall, behind which part of the wall, the stable was where my father and we were.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So that he could throw it over, maybe somebody will find it.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "He told us later that he went, but the train to Auschwitz had already left.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "It left something like 6 o'clock in the morning.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Now, immediately my brother and I were brought-- transferred from the convent, where no men were allowed in, only women-- to a Catholic orphanage in another part of Florence, called Rifredi.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And the orphanage was called Madonnina Del Grappa, under the direction of Don Giulio Facibeni.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] We were brought there and Don Giovanni accompanied us to the orphanage.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And we were handed over.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "We were brought in to see Don Facibeni, the director.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And only he and his assistant, Don Nello, knew we were Jews.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "We concocted a whole story, because we're going to be mingled with the other children who were all Catholic.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And the story was that we were children of Italian parents caught behind British lines.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "My mother.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "The father is Italian, but on the Russian front somewhere.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
